While investigating adding support for custom union types to Polly's [`Outcome<T>`](https://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/blob/main/src/Polly.Core/Outcome.TResult.cs) type which conceptually represents either the result of an operation or an exception from that operation (https://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/pull/3020), I found that a number of our tests were failing.

The root cause was eventually found to be due to conditions like the below never evaluating to true:

```csharp
Outcome<T>? maybeOutcome = Something();

if (maybeOutcome is Outcome<T> outcome)
{
    return outcome;
}
```

Fixing the code paths required changing the code to patterns like:

```csharp
if (maybeOutcome.HasValue)
{
    return maybeOutcome.GetValueOrDefault();
}
```

**Version Used**: .NET SDK `11.0.100-preview.2.26159.112`

**Steps to Reproduce**:

Run the following code snippet with `dotnet run Program.cs`:

```csharp
#:property LangVersion=preview

// Remove this for the application to behave as intended
#:property DefineConstants=UNIONS

#if UNIONS
using System.Runtime.CompilerServices;
#endif

return Repro(42);

static int Repro<T>(T value)
{
    var maybeOutcome = GetOutcome(value);

    if (maybeOutcome is Outcome<T> outcome)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"Success: {outcome.Result}");
        return 0;
    }
    else
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Failure");
        return 1;
    }
}

static Outcome<T>? GetOutcome<T>(T result)
{
    return new Outcome<T>(result);
}

#if UNIONS
[Union]
public readonly struct Outcome<TResult>(TResult result) : IUnion
#else
public readonly struct Outcome<TResult>(TResult result)
#endif
{
    public TResult Result { get; } = result;

    public bool HasValue => true;

    public object? Value => Result;
}

#if UNIONS
namespace System.Runtime.CompilerServices
{
    public interface IUnion
    {
        object? Value { get; }
    }

    [AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Class | AttributeTargets.Struct, AllowMultiple = false)]
    public sealed class UnionAttribute : Attribute;
}
#endif
```

**Diagnostic Id**:

N/A

**Expected Behavior**:

`Success: 42` is printed to the console.

**Actual Behavior**:

`Failure` is printed to the console

